The paper proposes a method for unsupervised learning of disentangled representations, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of representation learning. The use of variational inference and regularizers suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling, which is often associated with the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the proposed method to image data (as mentioned in the abstract) suggests a potential fit with computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are common in representation learning, suggests a potential fit with the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
